Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife
through, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim the @Carrot{1}(trimmed), then halve lengthways (no need to peel).
Slice widthways into pieces about 1cm thick.

Halve, peel and chop the @Onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces) into
small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion and carrot. Fry until softened, ~{6-7%minutes}.

While the veg is frying, trim the @Green Beans{150%grams}(trimmed), then spread
them out on a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{}
and @ground black pepper{}.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until tender, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, remove the @Slow Cooked Beef{280%grams} from the packet and cut into
2cm chunks (reserve the juices in the packet to add later).

> If you'd prefer to boil your green beans, boil them in step 4 while the sauce
> simmers for 4-6 mins, until tender.

Once the veg has softened, add the beef and its juices, @Red Wine Jus Paste{15%grams},
@Red Wine Stock Paste{28%grams}, @Tomato Puree{30%grams}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and
@Water for the Sauce{100%milliliter} to the pan.

> TIP: If your red wine jus paste has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water
> for 1 min.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure the beef is piping hot throughout.

Once thickened, stir in the @Butter{20%grams} until melted. Add a splash of
water if it's a little too thick.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan,
off the heat.

Add a knob of @Butter{} and a splash of @?milk{} and mash until smooth.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Cover with a #lid{} to keep
warm.

Share the brisket style beef between your #bowls{}.

Serve the mash and green beans alongside. Enjoy!